<subSubSection pageId="139" pageNumber="140" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
SOCOTRA, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Balfour et al.</emphasis>
302 (holotype K!; isotype OXF!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="140" lastPageNumber="141" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="140" lastPageNumber="141" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
Perennial herb with numerous decumbent stems to 30 cm long, vegetative parts densely greyish strigose-pubescent when young but indumentum much sparser on older parts. Leaves forming a somewhat persistent basal rosette, sessile, 0.8-2.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.8 cm, obovate to oblanceolate, apex obtuse, margin entire, at base attenuate into a pseudopetiole, densely silvery strigose; stem leaves narrower upwards 
<pageBreakToken pageId="140" pageNumber="141" start="start">and</pageBreakToken>
merging with bracts, thinly strigose. Inflorescence a raceme-like thyrse formed of single-flowered cymes; peduncles 2-10(-16) mm long; bracteoles 1-3 mm long, filiform to narrowly elliptic; pedicels 3-5 mm long; outer sepals 2.5-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2 mm, ovate, acute, green with scarious margin; corolla (7-)9-11 mm long, white, unlobed, midpetaline bands strigose; ovary glabrous; style white, glabrous, divided c. 2 mm above base, stigmas 2.5 mm, red. [
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, AG" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 759" refId="B234" refString="Miller, AG, Morris, M, 2004. Ethnoflora of the Soqotra Archipelago. Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh: 1 - 759" title="Ethnoflora of the Soqotra Archipelago" year="2004">Miller and Morris 2004</bibRefCitation>
: 517]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="140" pageNumber="141" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
Yemen: Socotra (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Miller et al.</emphasis>
10221, 10191, 19107) and Hadramaut (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Thulin &amp; Gifri</emphasis>
8652; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Thulin et al.</emphasis>
8196).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="140" pageNumber="141" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
The sericeous basal leaves separate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Balf. f., Proc. Roy. Soc. Edinburgh 12: 83. 1884. (Balfour" authorityYear="1884" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sarmentosus" order="Solanales" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sarmentosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Convolvulus sarmentosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hildebrandtii" order="Solanales" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hildebrandtii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Convolvulus hildebrandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the entire leaf margin from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Balf. f., Nat. Hist. Sokotra 524. 1903. (Forbes" authorityYear="1903" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus grantii" order="Solanales" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grantii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Convolvulus grantii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Mature specimens without basal parts can be confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hildebrandtii" order="Solanales" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hildebrandtii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Convolvulus hildebrandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the stems are herbaceous and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“leafy,”">&quot;leafy,&quot;</normalizedToken>
the bracts oblong-oblanceolate, rather than linear.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
